name: UDP-N-acetyl-D-mannosamine dehydrogenase
classes: Acting on the CH-OH group of donors;
With NAD+ or NADP+ as acceptor
reaction: UDP-N-acetyl-alpha-D-mannosamine + 2 NAD+ + H2O = UDP-N-acetyl-alpha-D-mannosaminuronate + 2 NADH + 2 H+ [RN:R03317]
comment: Part of the pathway for acetamido sugar biosynthesis in bacteria and archaea. The enzyme has no activity with NADP+.

pathways.ec00520: Amino sugar and nucleotide sugar metabolism

references.title: Acetamido sugar biosynthesis in the Euryarchaea.
